Introduction:

This dataset comprises of Algerian Forest Fire Dataset taken from UCI. Link of the dataset is as follows :- https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Algerian+Forest+Fires+Dataset++ . This Model Predicts using Logistic Regression Algorithm that whether there will be a fire or not in the Algerian Forest on the basis of various given circumstances in the data. This dataset includes 244 instances that regroup a data of 2 regions of Algeria,namely the Brjajia region located in the northeast of Algeria and the Sidi Belabbes region located in the northwest of Algeria. 122 instances for each region. The Period is from June 2012 to September 2012.The Dataset includes 11 attributes and 1 output attribute i.e. Classes. The data consists of 14 column and 246 rows. In the parts below, I will use logistic regression, LDA, QDA, and decison methods to see which method works better for this dataset. In the separate R file, I will use KNN method.

In [37]:
def Feature_Scaling(X_train, X_test):
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    X_train_after_Standardisation = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
    X_test_after_Standardisation = scaler.transform(X_test)
    return X_train_after_Standardisation, X_test_after_Standardisation
